The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | GM unveils Cruze 
                                                                                                               GM unveils Cruze 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Oct. 12: General Motors India, which launched the Chevrolet Cruze today, said it had lined up a slew of car launches in the months ahead.         
	The auto maker plans to launch the Chevrolet Beat in January and a mid-size sedan in the next 18 months.        
	All these cars are part of our new 300 series platform or the third-generation cars. More cars will be launched under the new series, said Ankush Arora, head of sales and marketing, GM India.         
	The Cruze has been been priced in the range of Rs 10.99 lakh to Rs 12.45 lakh (ex-showroom, Delhi). The company has rolled out two variants of this sedan, which features a two-litre diesel engine. Pitted against Skodas Laura, Hondas Civic, Volkwagens Jetta and Toyotas Corolla Altis, the Chevrolet Cruze has already got 1,200 bookings.                                                                                                                                        
